5 title, a certified physician assistant, or a certified Advanced
6 Practice Registered Nurse. A laser practitioner who is not a
7 physician shall complete a laser practitioner training and education
8 program. A laser training and education program may be completed
9 internally at the laser hair removal facility or via a third party,
10 provided such third-party program is overseen by a physician. A
11 laser practitioner training and education program shall include
12 forty (40) total hours of training, which may be a combination of
13 didactic training, in-person hands-on training, and performance of
14 laser hair removal procedures.
15 C. A laser hair removal facility shall be overseen by a
16 physician; provided, that Advanced Practice Registered Nurses shall
17 be exempt from this oversight requirement, as defined in paragraphs
18 1 through 6 of subsection A of Section 725.2 of this title, a
19 certified physician assistant, or a certified Advanced Practice
20 Registered Nurse.
21 D. The overseeing physician shall:
22 1. Establish proper protocols for laser hair removal provided
23 at a facility including, but not limited to, complication
24 management. A laser practitioner shall follow all written procedure
